🎯 Ansible Concepts You Must Know (Mid-Level DevOps Engineer)
1️⃣ Ansible Architecture (Very Important)
Understand:

Agentless architecture

Control node vs Managed nodes

SSH based communication

Push model

You should clearly explain:

“Ansible uses agentless SSH-based push model. Control node executes modules remotely.”

2️⃣ Inventory Management
You must know:

Static inventory (INI format)

YAML inventory

Grouping hosts

Host variables

Group variables

Example:

[web]
server1
server2

[db]
db1
Real-world skill:

Maintain different inventories for dev, qa, prod

3️⃣ Ansible Ad-Hoc Commands
Very important for troubleshooting.

ansible all -m ping
ansible web -m shell -a "df -h"
You should know:

ping

copy

yum / apt

service

shell

command

Mid-level engineer uses ad-hoc daily.

4️⃣ Playbooks (Core Concept)
This is the heart.

You must understand:

YAML structure

hosts

tasks

become

vars

handlers

Example structure:

- name: Install Nginx
  hosts: web
  become: yes
  tasks:
    - name: Install nginx
      yum:
        name: nginx
        state: present
5️⃣ Modules (Important Ones Only)
You don't need all 3000 modules.

Focus on:

yum / apt

service

copy

template

file

user

group

git

docker_container

k8s

uri

These cover 80% real projects.

6️⃣ Variables & Variable Precedence
Must know:

vars

vars_files

host_vars

group_vars

extra-vars

precedence order (basic idea)

In interviews they ask:

Which variable overrides which?

7️⃣ Handlers
Very important for real automation.

Example:

notify: restart nginx
Understand:

Triggered only when task changes

Runs at end of play

8️⃣ Templates (Jinja2)
Used everywhere.

You must know:

{{ variable }}

if condition

loops

Example:

server_name {{ domain_name }};
Used for:

nginx configs

app configs

system configs

9️⃣ Loops & Conditionals
Very important.

loop:
  - nginx
  - git
Conditions:

when: ansible_os_family == "RedHat"
🔟 Roles (VERY IMPORTANT)
This separates beginner from professional.

Understand:

Standard role structure:

roles/
  nginx/
    tasks/
    handlers/
    templates/
    vars/
    defaults/
Real projects use roles always.

1️⃣1️⃣ Ansible Galaxy
Know:

Install roles

requirements.yml

Using community roles

Example:

ansible-galaxy install geerlingguy.nginx
1️⃣2️⃣ Tags
Used in CI/CD.

tags:
  - install
Run specific part:

ansible-playbook site.yml --tags install
Very important in pipelines.

1️⃣3️⃣ Ansible Vault
Must know for security.

Encrypt:

Passwords

Secrets

API keys

ansible-vault encrypt secrets.yml
Interview favorite topic.

1️⃣4️⃣ Dynamic Inventory (Basic Understanding)
Know concept:

AWS dynamic inventory

Azure dynamic inventory

Kubernetes dynamic inventory

You don’t need to master — just understand.

1️⃣5️⃣ Ansible with Docker
Important for YOU since you focus Docker.

Know:

Install Docker using playbook

Deploy container

Pull images

Manage containers

Module:

community.docker.docker_container

1️⃣6️⃣ Ansible with Kubernetes
Just basic:

Deploy YAML to cluster

Use k8s module

You don’t need deep knowledge — Kubernetes native tools preferred.

1️⃣7️⃣ Error Handling
Understand:

ignore_errors

failed_when

changed_when

retries

until

1️⃣8️⃣ Idempotency (VERY IMPORTANT)
You must clearly explain:

Ansible ensures desired state. Running playbook multiple times should not change system if already configured.

This is core DevOps concept.

1️⃣9️⃣ CI/CD Integration
Know how to:

Run playbooks from Jenkins

Pass extra-vars

Use vault in pipelines

(Like your Jenkins API issues you were debugging earlier.)

2️⃣0️⃣ Ansible Project Structure (Professional Level)
Know how to structure:

inventories/
  dev/
  prod/
roles/
playbooks/
group_vars/
host_vars/
This makes you mid-level engineer.

